data.meta_description: Actress. Born Paula Osterman in Sonora, Mexico, she made her debut in films appearing in White Shadows of the South Seas (1928). She went on to be screen beauty in films to include The Desert Rider (1930), Aloha (1931), The Woman I Stole (1933), Duck Soup (1933), Red Wagon (1933) and Go West Young Man (1936). She was...
